# Three edge services, one job

Every request starts with a **DNS lookup**, then bytes travel to your origin over a fixed speed of light. Three edge services attack **three layers** — all "get the user to the right endpoint, **fast**."

## Route 53 — DNS

Authoritative **DNS**: answers lookups, decides **which endpoint** (routing policies + health checks).

## CloudFront — CDN

Hundreds of edges **cache** content close to users, absorb origin load, terminate **TLS** at the edge. HTTP(S) only.

## Global Accelerator — backbone

**No cache** — gets **TCP/UDP** traffic onto **AWS's backbone** at the nearest edge. **Static IPs**, network-speed failover.

**Layers:** DNS · caching · backbone → then a decision matrix.
